@@TJvSplitter.Create
Summary
  Creates and initializes a new TJvSplitter object.
Description
  Use \Create to create and initialize a new TJvSplitter object.

  \Create calls the inherited \Create method, then sets the initial values for the splitter control
  as follows:

  * HintColor is set to clInfoBk.
Parameters
  AOwner - A component, typically the form, that is responsible for freeing the splitter control.
See Also
  HintColor
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSplitter.HintColor
Summary
  Determines the color of the hint boxes for the Help Hints for the splitter control.
Description
  Use HintColor to specify the hint box color. A default color value of clInfoBk is set for the
  HintColor property in the constructor when the application is created. To change the HintColor
  assign it a new TColor value.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSplitter.OnMouseEnter
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves over the splitter control.
Description
  \Write an OnMouseEnter event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse over the
  splitter control. For example, you can use this event to change the font color when the mouse is over the
  splitter control, and then use the OnMouseLeave event to change it back when the mouse moves off the splitter control.
See Also
  OnMouseLeave
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSplitter.OnMouseLeave
Summary
  Occurs when the mouse pointer moves off the splitter control.
Description
  \Write an OnMouseLeave event handler to take specific action when the user moves the mouse off the
  splitter control. For example, you can use this event to undo changes that were made in an OnMouseEnter
  event handler.
See Also
  OnMouseEnter
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvSplitter.OnParentColorChange
Summary
  Occurs when the color property for the parent of the splitter control changes.
Description
  \Write an OnParentColorChange event to take specific action when the ParentColor property changes.
